sg.edu.cs2103aug2015_w13_2j.parser

Class Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • sg.edu.cs2103aug2015_w13_2j.parser.Parser

  • public class Parser
extends java.lang.Object
    Parser class that handles the interpretation of tokens within the user's command input. This class ensures that all tokens of the user command are of a specific Token type.
    Author:
    Zhu Chunqi

      • parseCommand

        public Command parseCommand(Logic logic,
                            java.lang.String command)
        Parses the provided command string into a Command object. Invalid tokens are marked with _INVALID after the Token type.
        Parameters:
        logic - Dependency injection of a LogicInterface component which is used by this Parser component to determine the reserved keyword strings.
        command - Command string to parse.
        Returns:
        A Iterable Command object containing parsed Tokens.

      • getParsedTokens

      • parseDate

        public static java.lang.String parseDate(java.lang.String datetime)
                                  throws IllegalDateFormatException
        Attempts to parse the provided date string and return a string representation in the format dd_MM_yyyy_HH_mm to be used by SimpleDateFormat to fill the unspecified parts from a base date. Supported date string formats are any combination of date and time formats as listed below. An exception will be thrown if the provided date string does not conform to any supported format. Bounds checking is not performed for day, month, year, hour or minute values.
        • dd/mm/yyyy
        • dd/mm
        • dd
        • Thh:mm
        • Thh
        Parameters:
        datetime - Date string to be parsed.
        Returns:
        String in the format dd_MM_yyyy_HH_mm. Fields which are defined in the date string are filled in.
        Throws:
        IllegalDateFormatException - Thrown when the date string is not of a valid format.

      • updateDate

        public static java.util.Date updateDate(java.lang.String format,
                                        java.util.Date baseDate)
        Attempts to update the fields of the provided base Date to match that in the format string. Throws an exception when the format string contains values which are out of bounds for their corresponding fields.
        Parameters:
        format - String of the format dd_MM_yyyy_HH_mm as produced by parseDate(String).
        baseDate - Base Date object to be updated, does not check for null.
        Returns:
        Updated Date object if there were no parse errors or the original Date object otherwise.
